doomgeneric (vendored)
======================

Origin: https://github.com/ozkl/doomgeneric
License: GNU General Public License v2 (see ./LICENSE)

doomgeneric is a portable port of id Software's DOOM that reduces the
platform layer to a handful of DG_* callbacks. This directory vendors the
subset of the C engine that the `doom` cog compiles via build.rs (the
`cc` crate). We deliberately DO NOT vendor any of the upstream platform
backends (doomgeneric_sdl.c, _xlib.c, _allegro.c, _win.c, _soso*.c,
_linuxvt.c, _emscripten.c) — the cog provides its own headless DG_*
backend in ../../src/main.rs. The SDL/Allegro sound mixers are likewise
omitted; the engine builds against the generic sound stub (no audio out).

Why vendored (not a submodule):
  * The PR is self-contained and CI (`cargo check`) builds without
    `git submodule update`.
  * The exact source set we compile is pinned and reviewable in-tree.

Licensing note:
  doomgeneric and the original DOOM source it derives from are GPLv2.
  Linking this engine makes the `doom` cog binary a GPLv2 derivative —
  hence the `doom` cog ships under GPLv2 (see ../../LICENSE and
  ../../NOTICE) even though the rest of the cognitum-one/cogs repo is
  MIT. No DOOM game data (WAD) is vendored here; the cog uses the
  freely-redistributable FreeDoom IWAD as a runtime asset.
